Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
saveBlackBox(25.10)                                        saveBlackBox(25.10)

Name
       saveBlackBox  -  Creates a blackbox LEF file containing the pin defini-
       tions and obstructions

Syntax
       saveBlackBox

       [-help]

       {<instName> | -all}

       [-5.6]

       [-lefFile <string>]

       Creates a blackbox LEF file containing the pin definitions and obstruc-
       tions.

       Note: The savePartition command also  automatically  saves  this  file,
       among others.

Parameters
       -5.6   Specifies the LEF file format version.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -all   Specifies all blackbox instances.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each saveBlackBox parameter. For a detailed  de-
              scription  of the command and all of its parameters, use the man
              command: man saveBlackBox

       <instName>
              Specifies the name of the blackbox instance. You can  use  wild-
              cards (*?) with this parameter.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -lefFile <string>
              Specifies  the  LEF  filename. If you do not specify a name, the
              default is <cellTypeName>.lef.

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
       The following command creates a LEF file containing the pin definitions
       and obstructions for all blackbox instances that start with the  letter
       A to a LEF file named BBox.lef:

       saveBlackBox A* -lefFile BBox.lef

